Create the Revenue Operations Analytics App

A guided flow walks you through creating an app from the Revenue Operations Analytics template.

Required Editions and User Permissions
Available with CRM Analytics, available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition. Requires a CRM Analytics Plus license.
CRM Analytics Plus Admin permission set is needed to create and manage the Revenue Operations Analytics app.
CRM Analytics Plus User permission set is needed to use the Revenue Operations Analytics app.

Before you create an app, make sure that:
You have at least one record for each of the Opportunity, Account, Forecasting Item, Forecasting Type, User, and UserRole objects.
The Analytics Integration User has the appropriate Salesforce field-level security to view the fields used in the app.

From the Analytics tab or Analytics Studio, click Create and then select App.
Select the Revenue Operations Analytics template to open the guided flow.
Name and save your app.
To create snapshots of your opportunity data for period-over-period comparisons, schedule your app to refresh.
The Revenue Operations Analytics app creates two dataflows, one to process the revenue data and another for opportunity data snapshots.

Upload a Quota Dataset to the Revenue Operations Analytics App

Required Editions and User Permissions
Available with CRM Analytics, available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.
Requires a CRM Analytics Plus license.
CRM Analytics Plus Admin permission set is needed to create and manage the app.

To use the app: You need at least one record for each of the Opportunity, Account, Forecasting Item, Forecasting Type, User, and UserRole objects.
The Analytics Integration User has the appropriate Salesforce field-level security to view the fields used in the app.

Schedule your app to refresh to create snapshots of your opportunity data for period-over-period comparisons.
